---
description: How to use and develop the SentientUI MCP server
alwaysApply: true
---

This repo is `@sentientui/mcp`, the MCP server for SentientUI (adaptive UI
personalization — https://sentient-ui.com).

Connecting an assistant to SentientUI:
- Hosted: `https://api.sentient-ui.com/mcp` (Streamable HTTP + OAuth, no key).
  Claude Code: `claude mcp add --transport http sentientui https://api.sentient-ui.com/mcp`.
- Local: `npx @sentientui/mcp` with `SENTIENTUI_API_KEY=sk_...` (omit for demo mode).

Tools read experiment data (variant performance, personas, goal funnels, insights,
guardrail events) and manage projects/variants. See README.md for the full list.

Developing this package:
- `src/server.ts` builds the server; `src/tools/*` register tools; `src/api-client.ts`
  calls the SentientUI management API.
- `pnpm build` (tsup) · `pnpm test` (vitest) · `pnpm typecheck`.
- No secrets belong in this repo. Every tool must map to a real management endpoint.
- Don't rename a public tool without a changeset — clients depend on the names.
